rComments: She is a nice person, but her assignments are overwhelming and frustrating. Honestly, I don't think watching a 1:20 mins video to write a humour analysis report with 7-10 pages, 1.5 spaced is really necessary (plus, the video wasn't funny at all!). She also didn't provide any written feedback for the assignment even though I have emailed her.

I cant believe how amazing this professor this. She truly cares about her students, she will make SURE that you succeed! She's caring and compassionate and a real gem. I was blessed to have been in her class, i hope i will have her again. Show up for online lectures, try to participate and do your work and you will pass.

I took her class during summer and she was great! The class is super interesting and pretty easy to follow, since she explains everything so well. Plus, her slides are super detailed, so you can pretty much get away with just studying those and the assignments are very straightforward. Would definitely take again!

Professor Pare is probably one of the easiest markers at the university. She's also really nice and funny, and she wants everyone to participate in class. Her background is in humour studies, so a lot of her material revolves around that.

Prof Paré is an absolute gem. The class itself was incredibly interesting (l'humour en temps de crise) and you can tell she really cares about her students. There was a lot of writing in her course, but that is my strong suit so I didn't mind. As an anglophone, I found her to be very clear and easy to understand.

I wanted to like Professor Paré, as she is kind & accommodating. This course, however, was THE most confusing I've ever taken. She regularly circled back to concepts we'd already covered but provided new definitions. She told us on WEEK 9 not to read an assigned book that many had already finished. Content should be easy- she makes it impossible.
